edu.cmu.lti.oaqa.bio.resource_wrapper.xml
Class XMLNode

java.lang.Object
  edu.cmu.lti.oaqa.bio.resource_wrapper.xml.XMLNode

public class XMLNode
extends java.lang.Object

A tree node (of XMLTree) that represents a Node within a Document (XML).
Designed to make the output from Entrez Gene easier to work with.

Version:
1.0.1
Author:
Collin McCormack (cmccorma)
See Also:
Node, Document, XMLTree

findAll

public java.util.ArrayList<XMLNode> findAll(java.lang.String name,

Searches the children of this node and finds all occurrences of a node with the input name (case-sensitive). Can search all children of this node or just the immediate children.

Parameters:

recursive - if true, search ALL children, otherwise only immediate children

findOne

Parameters:
name - The name to look for
recursive - If true, search all children, otherwise search immediate children only
